# Mock server and fixtures

`apps/mock-server` serves the mock JSON fixtures behind a REST-shaped
API (via `json-server`) so `@gridyard/workspace-runtime`'s REST adapter
(`docs/04-layout-and-permission-engine-spec.md`) has something real to
point at before an actual backend exists.

- Fixtures live in `apps/mock-server/db.json`, one top-level collection
  per entity (`loans`, `employees`, `invoices`, and so on).
- A new workspace definition that needs mock data should add a new
  collection here rather than inlining fixture data inside application
  or package code.
- Keep fixture data consistent with the examples already used across
  `docs/03-workspace-schema-spec.md` and the UI mockups (same borrower
  names, same field names) — it makes it obvious when a spec example
  and the running mock diverge.
- This is a development-time stand-in, not a real adapter
  implementation — don't add real business logic (validation,
  computed fields, auth) here. That belongs in
  `@gridyard/workspace-runtime` once a real adapter is built.
